        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "# Stability Constants (log β) for DTPA with Various Metals\n\n**DTPA** (diethylenetriaminepentaacetic acid, ligand_6356) is one of the strongest aminopolycarboxylate chelators known. Here are the **1:1 formation constants** for the reaction **M + L ⇌ ML** at **25 °C, I = 0.1 M** in water, from the NIST SRD-46 database:\n\n| Metal | log β (ML) | Electrolyte |\n|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| Bi³⁺ | **33.62** | KNO₃ |\n| Fe³⁺ | **28.60** | KNO₃ |\n| Fe³⁺ | 28.02 | NaClO₄ |\n| Th⁴⁺ | 26.64 | NaClO₄ |\n| Ga³⁺ | **25.19** | KNO₃ |\n| Yb³⁺ | **22.62** | KNO₃ |\n| Eu³⁺ | **22.39** | KNO₃ |\n| Sm³⁺ | **22.34** | KNO₃ |\n| Nd³⁺ | **21.60** | KNO₃ |\n| Cu²⁺ | **21.53** | KNO₃ |\n| Th⁴⁺ | 21.40 | KNO₃ |\n| Ni²⁺ | **20.32** | KNO₃ |\n| Cd²⁺ | **19.31** | KNO₃ |\n| Co²⁺ | **19.26** | KNO₃ |\n| Pb²⁺ | **18.80** | KNO₃ |\n| Zn²⁺ | **18.75** | KNO₃ |\n| Al³⁺ | **18.40** | KNO₃ |\n| Fe²⁺ | **16.55** | KNO₃ |\n| Mn²⁺ | **15.60** | KNO₃ |\n| Ca²⁺ | **10.74** | KNO₃ |\n| Mg²⁺ | **9.30** | KNO₃ |",
